
This holds a single play to do a complete setup for the ALA demo platform on CentOS.  

This is a monolythic installation - future iterations might split out roles correctly, to allow for a more sophisticated deployment topology (e.g. roles for cassandra, web, tomcat etc).

Example to run this using a the vagrant and insecure private key:
$ ansible-playbook -i vagrant site.yml --private-key /Users/tim/.vagrant.d/insecure_private_key 